Package gameobjects

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    NPC.Strategy
    Interface for the strategy that the interface uses, this will be defined as two strategies: a random strategy and a circle strategy
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Building
    Class that holds all the information to do with the Building object within the game, this is a couple of special messages that distinguish the objects such as file names and what type of item it is within the toString method
    Chest
    Class that holds all the information to do with the Chest object within the game, this is its file name and the code and contents of the chest
    Door
    Class that holds all the information to do with the Door object within the game, such as the door position, the code of the door and the locationID
    Fence
    Class that holds all the information to do with the Fence object within the game, such as the location of the fence
    GameObject
    Abstract class that holds all the information for GameObjects, these are objects such as Doors, Wall and Fences.
    NPC
    Class that holds all the information for an NPC within the game, using a strategy interface it selects a strategy to use during the game
    Player
    Class that holds all the information for the players within the game, such as their name and their current location
    Tree
    Class that holds all the information to do with the Tree object within the game, this is a couple of special messages that distinguish the objects such as file names and what type of item it is within the toString method
    Wall
    Class that holds all the information to do with the wall object within the game, this is its file name and the code and its description
